    "189311 eading Daily Newspaper of Western Colorado1910 THIS IS THE PAPER THAT HAS BEEN BOOSTING GRAND JUNCTION FOR TWENTY YEARS AND IS STILL ON THE JOB VOL XVIIL TAYLOR LEADS STEVENS BY 4500 Sentinel Special Service Denver Nov 15At democratic headquarters this afternoon Chair man Bradley announced that Con greassman E T Taylor was leading I N Stevens by 4500 plurality This is due to the fact that democratic headquarters has returns from more counties than has republican head quarters He said that he believed that At torney General Barnett was reelect ed but that he had no figures to give out He also claims that Judge Gun ter is running close for supreme court At republican headquarters Grll fiths election is claimed by 1335 plurality and while they are not giving out any figures yet the re _ publicans say that I N Stevens ls running a few hundred ahead of Tay lor According to the count thus far Judge Gunter has gained about 200 votes in Baca and Summit counties as well as in some of the hitherto un reported precincts It is claimed that a large number of the students at Colorado college allowed their enthusiasm for"
